 1 release, weâ€™ve madeÂ <a href=\"https://core.trac.wordpress.org/log/trunk/?action=stop_on_copy&amp;mode=stop_on_copy&amp;rev=41846&amp;stop_rev=41777&amp;limit=100&amp;sfp_email=&amp;sfph_mail=\">70 changes</a>Â in Beta 2, andÂ <a href=\"https://core.trac.wordpress.org/log/trunk/?action=stop_on_copy&amp;mode=stop_on_copy&amp;rev=41938&amp;stop_rev=41847&amp;limit=100&amp;sfp_email=&amp;sfph_mail=\">92 changes</a> in <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/news/2017/10/wordpress-4-9-beta-3/\">Beta 3</a>. In Beta 4, we&#8217;ve madeÂ <a href=\"https://core.trac.wordpress.org/log/trunk/?action=stop_on_copy&amp;mode=stop_on_copy&amp;rev=42020&amp;stop_rev=41940&amp;limit=100&amp;sfp_email=&amp;sfph_mail=\">80 changes</a>, focusing on bug fixes and finalizing new features.</p>\n<p>Do you speak a language other than English?Â <a href=\"https://translate.wordpress.org/projects/wp/dev\">Help us translate WordPress into more than 100 languages!</a></p>\n<p><strong>If you think youâ€™ve found a bug</strong>, you can post to theÂ <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/forum/alphabeta\">Alpha/Beta area</a>Â in the support forums. Weâ€™d love to hear from you! If youâ€™re comfortable writing a reproducible bug report,Â <a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/core/reports/\">file one on WordPress Trac</a>, where you can also findÂ <a href=\"https://core.trac.wordpress.org/tickets/major\">a list of known bugs</a>.</p>\n<p><i>Beta 4 at last,<br />\nRC 1 draws ever near.<br />\nLet&#8217;s make it bug-free. <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/2.3/72x72/1f41b.png\" alt=\"?\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/2.3/72x72/1f6ab.png\" alt=\"?\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></i></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:30:\"com-wordpress:feed-additions:1\";a:1:{s:7:\"post-id\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4