lendar.com/maintenance-release-for-the-week-of-18-december-2017/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">4.4.20 release</a> which led to events displaying in the wrong order under some circumstances. No other plugins are impacted.</p>\n<p>If you have a valid license key then you should be able to take advantage of automated updates, or else you can download the latest version from the <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/my-account/downloads/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">My Account &rarr; Downloads</a> screen.</p>\n<p>Thanks for your patience and support while we worked on this issue <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/2.3/72x72/1f642.png\" alt=\"?\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/hotfix-for-events-calendar-pro-4-4-20-1/\">Hotfix for Events Calendar PRO (4.4.20.1)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:52:\"Maintenance Release for the Week of 18 December 2017\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:83:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-for-the-week-of-18-december-2017/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 18 Dec 2017 22:56:36 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Products\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1408019\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:636:\"<p>Welcome to Maintenance Release number 25 and last planned release of 2017! Serving our community with 25 maintenance releases this year has been an incredibly rewarding task and we&#8217;d like to thank each and everyone of you for your patience, diligence and well crafted support tickets that have all helped in squashing bugs and creating&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-for-the-week-of-18-december-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 18 December 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Neill McShea\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6743:\"<p>Welcome to Maintenance Release number 25 and last planned release of 2017! Serving our community with 25 maintenance releases this year has been an incredibly rewarding task and we&#8217;d like to thank each and everyone of you for your patience, diligence and well crafted support tickets that have all helped in squashing bugs and creating fixes! If this is your first time getting an update from us remember Maintenance Releases are smaller updates between major releases that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements. We always recommend using a staging site to test these changes before updating on a live site.</p>\n<p>To see all of the changes included in this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#pro\">The Events Calendar Pro 4.4.20</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#tec\">The Events Calendar 4.6.8</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#fb\">Filter Bar 4.5.2</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"pro\">The Events Calendar Pro 4.4.20</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Select2 for Widget filtering allows Searching correctly again\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Altered the collapse_sql logic to avoid SQL errors relating to query ordering (our thanks to Luke Kenny for flagging this problem)\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Added code to avoid running the min/max coordinates query when event IDs are available (doing so resulted in database errors &#8211; props @afragen)\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed an issue that would generate warnings on PHP 7.1+ (props to @tanumstrand)\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed a typo in the Event List widget options\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Prevent a fatal if a non-truthy value is passed when calling tribe_is_recurring_event()\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed strtotime() warnings on recurring events created past the last advance limit, props to Zoe for bringing this up\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Resolved an issue preventing us from using the correct singular or plural form for years within the recurrence UI (our thanks to websource for flagging this problem)\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed an issue with the [tribe_events] shortcode&#8217;s Day View where it wouldn&#8217;t paginate unless the Tribe Bar was activated (props to @socialspdlc-org for highlighting this issue)\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed some recurring event meta data-related code that would sometimes produce PHP notices when viewing events that recurred yearly (thanks @alistek for reporting this bug)\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed the mini calendar widget and shortcode&#8217;s pagination to ensure that each month shows a correct list of events (thanks to @kdr4phtc for reporting this)\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added Google Maps API key to all Google Maps URLs when the key is available, allowing maps to load more reliably on some hosting environments (props to @sfdfortnight, @thor, and many others for reporting this!)\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Modified recurrence dependency trigger to work with events with no ID\n<li><strong>Language</strong>  &#8211; 0 new strings added, 135 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 1 obsoleted\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"tec\">The Events Calendar 4.6.8</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Preserve filter bar checkbox selections when changing views\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fix radio filters so they are only included as values when switching views when checked\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Ensure the correct properties are set for list widget queries, to avoid problems when running alongside Events Calendar PRO (props @KZeni)\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed some layout issues with the &#8220;Buy Now&#8221; button and stock labels on mobile list views\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed issue where left- or right-aligned images at the bottom of event descriptions would overlap event meta on single-event pages\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed issue where Google Maps Link would display in some situations even when there is no address information for which to generate a link.\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Corrected reference to a Select2 asset (our thanks to @pyxis630 for flagging this problem and props to @andrasguseo for the fix)\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Ensure that when start and end dates are passed to the REST API, all events within the date range are correctly retrieved (thanks @braffenberg and others for highlighting this issue!)\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added Google Maps API key to all Google Maps URLs when the key is available, allowing maps to load more reliably on some hosting environments (props to @sfdfortnight, @thor, and many others for reporting this!)\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Adjusted CSS to improve the display of venue URLs/phone numbers (especially when Events Calendar PRO is also active) (our thanks to Mathew on the forums for flagging this issue)\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added new REST API endpoint that allows looking up events by slug instead of ID at the path `events/by-slug/{slug}/`, it has the same functionality as the endpoint `events/{ID}`\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added `slug` to the REST API responses for event data\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added `slug` to the REST API parameters allowed to use when inserting or updating an event\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added new `tribe_events_rest_use_inclusive_start_end_dates` filter so that users can make the REST API return events from a more literal date range\n<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; 3 new strings added, 68 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 0 obsoleted\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"fb\">Filter Bar 4.5.2</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fix PHP notice &#8220;Trying to get property of non-object&#8221; when checking category depth, thanks Simon!\n<li><strong>Compatibility</strong> &#8211; Minimum supported version of WordPress in now 4.5\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</h3>\n<p>The following plugins have not been updated this release and will remain at the version numbers specified here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Event Tickets 4.6.2</li>\n<li>Event Tickets Plus 4.6.2</li>\n<li>Community Events 4.5.8</li>\n<li>Community Tickets 4.5.3</li>\n<li>Image Widget 4.4.7</li>\n<li>Advanced Post Manager 4.4</li>\n<li>Eventbrite Tickets 4.4.8</li>\n<li>Image Widget Plus 1.0.2</li>\n<li>GigPress 2.3.19</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-for-the-week-of-18-december-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 18 December 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"Maintenance Release for the Week of 3 December 2017\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-3-december-2017/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 07 Dec 2017 18:51:01 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Products\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1399953\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:610:\"<p>Welcome to Maintenance Release number 24 of 2017! Here are some fixes and tweaks for you, to help your plugins run more smoothly. If this is your first time getting an update from us remember Maintenance Releases are smaller updates between major releases that are mostly comprised of bug Fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-3-december-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 3 December 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Victor\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7598:\"<p>Welcome to Maintenance Release number 24 of 2017! Here are some fixes and tweaks for you, to help your plugins run more smoothly. If this is your first time getting an update from us remember Maintenance Releases are smaller updates between major releases that are mostly comprised of bug Fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements. We always recommend using a staging site to test these changes before updating on a live site.</p>\n<p>To see all of the changes included in this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#tec\">The Events Calendar 4.6.7</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#et\">Event Tickets 4.6.2</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#etp\">Event Tickets Plus 4.6.2</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ct\">Community Tickets 4.5.3</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"tec\">The Events Calendar 4.6.6</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed broken RSVP ticket sales when using Aggregator CSV</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Prevent non-escaped underscores from getting into the final SQL for LIKE queries (Props to @misenhower)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed sorting for Tickets so that moving them to the first and last position of the order is allowed</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Improved handling of Stock to ensure it&#8217;s updated accordingly based on total sales when updating capacity</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Improved CSS for Capacity Table on mobile</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed some bugs with attendees management that prevented check-in features from working in Community Tickets front-end views (props @musician4you and several other folks for highlighting this issue)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Introduced the <sample>tribe_tickets_event_action_links_edit_url</sample> filter for more granular control over &#8220;edit event&#8221; links in various views</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Prevent EDD from being a provider for front-end Community Tickets, as only WooCommerce is allowed for that</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added actions: <sample>event_tickets_ticket_list_before_ticket_name</sample>, <sample>event_tickets_ticket_list_after_ticket_name</sample></li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; 0 new strings added, 54 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 0 obsoleted</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"et\">Event Tickets 4.6.2</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed broken RSVP ticket sales when using Aggregator CSV</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Prevent non-escaped underscores from getting into the final SQL for LIKE queries (Props to @misenhower)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed sorting for Tickets so that moving them to the first and last position of the order is allowed</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Improved handling of Stock to ensure it&#8217;s updated accordingly based on total sales when updating capacity</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Improved CSS for Capacity Table on mobile</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed some bugs with attendees management that prevented check-in features from working in Community Tickets front-end views (props @musician4you and several other folks for highlighting this issue)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Introduced the <sample>tribe_tickets_event_action_links_edit_url</sample> filter for more granular control over &#8220;edit event&#8221; links in various views</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Prevent EDD from being a provider for front-end Community Tickets, as only WooCommerce is allowed for that</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added actions: <sample>event_tickets_ticket_list_before_ticket_name</sample>, <sample>event_tickets_ticket_list_after_ticket_name</sample></li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; 0 new strings added, 54 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 0 obsoleted</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"etp\">Event Tickets Plus 4.6.2</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Make sure Stock is updated accordingly based on total sales when updating capacity</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Resolved bug where &#8220;Purchase limit&#8221; field was not saving correctly</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed an issue where the wrong number of tickets available would be shown in WooCommerce and Eeasy Digital Downloads purchase forms</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added filter to change the default value for the option to show attendees on the event, &#8216;tribe_tickets_plus_default_show_attendees_value&#8217;</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Prevent EDD from being a provider for front-end Community Tickets, as only WooCommerce is allowed for that</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Updated tooltip text for Capacity settings when using EDD</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Event capacity field will be enabled if never set via Ticket creation form</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Modified warning toggle with tribe prefix</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Avoid printing the SKU ticket fields on frontend forms (e.g. Community Event Tickets)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added helper text to selection of ecommerce plugin to clarify what that changes</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Decreased the width of the ticket capacity fields so they&#8217;re sized more proportionally to the values they hold</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Fixed some typos in names of deprecated properties on the Tribe__Tickets_Plus__Commerce__WooCommerce__Main class</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Resolved problems with importing sale time for tickets</li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; 2 new strings added, 24 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 0 obsoleted</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"ct\">Community Tickets 4.5.3</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Removed backend eCommerce links for all users on front end ticket form</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed some layout issues with the front-end &#8220;Order Report&#8221; view</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed some layout issues with the front-end &#8220;Attendees Report&#8221; view</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Made some changes to ensure the &#8220;edit&#8221; action links on front-end reports is only visible if users are allowed to edit submissions</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added CSS for new ticket alerts</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Fixed label CSS color in Twenty Seventeen theme</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Decreased the width of the ticket capacity fields so they&#8217;re sized more proportionally to the values they hold</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Prevent EDD tickets from being created on Community Tickets front-end, since only WooCommerce is supported for this feature</li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; 2 new strings added, 13 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 0 obsoleted</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</h3>\n<p>The following plugins have not been updated this release and will remain at the version numbers specified here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Events Calendar PRO 4.4.19</li>\n<li>Community Events 4.5.8</li>\n<li>Filter Bar 4.5.1</li>\n<li>Image Widget 4.4.7</li>\n<li>Advanced Post Manager 4.4</li>\n<li>Eventbrite Tickets 4.4.8</li>\n<li>Image Widget Plus 1.0.2</li>\n<li>GigPress 2.3.19</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-3-december-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 3 December 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:44:\"Event Tickets and Event Tickets Plus 4.6.1.1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/event-tickets-and-event-tickets-plus-4-6-1-1/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 24 Nov 2017 19:01:27 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1391031\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:616:\"<p>We&#8217;re pleased to announce the immediate availability of Event Tickets 4.6.1.1 and Event Tickets Plus 4.6.1.1 &#8212; both are available on the downloads page and for most users you will be able to update automatically from the comfort of your site&#8217;s dashboard soon. The focus here was on ensuring that start and end times for&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/event-tickets-and-event-tickets-plus-4-6-1-1/\">Event Tickets and Event Tickets Plus 4.6.1.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Barry\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1479:\"<p>We&#8217;re pleased to announce the immediate availability of Event Tickets 4.6.1.1 and Event Tickets Plus 4.6.1.1 &mdash; both are available on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/my-account/downloads/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">the downloads page</a> and for most users you will be able to update automatically from the comfort of your site&#8217;s dashboard soon.</p>\n<p>The focus here was on ensuring that start and end times for ticket sales are respected and that custom attendee field information is available to administrators. The changelogs can be found below and, as ever, please don&#8217;t hesitate to reach out to us <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/support/forums/forum/event-tickets/event-tickets-plus/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">on the forums</a> if you have any questions.</p>\n<h4>Event Tickets 4.6.1.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix &#8211; Respect Start and End time for ticket sales (props to Scott)</li>\n<li>Fix &#8211; Ensure attendee fields remain visible within the admin environment (compatibility fix for Event Tickets Plus)</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Event Tickets Plus 4.6.1.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix &#8211; Ensure attendee meta information is available within the admin environment</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/event-tickets-and-event-tickets-plus-4-6-1-1/\">Event Tickets and Event Tickets Plus 4.6.1.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"Nonprofit Spotlight: City Market\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/nonprofit-spotlight-city-market/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 22 Nov 2017 03:22:01 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"Nonprofit Spotlight\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1376422\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:596:\"<p>With the change in seasons just beginning to settle in and December holidays looming large on the horizon, there&#8217;s much to anticipate around this time of year. For many of us here in the United States, this week&#8217;s Thanksgiving holiday is a beloved annual occasion. It&#8217;s an opportunity to break bread with friends and family,&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/nonprofit-spotlight-city-market/\">Nonprofit Spotlight: City Market</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Caroline\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9009:\"<p>With the change in seasons just beginning to settle in and December holidays looming large on the horizon, there&#8217;s much to anticipate around this time of year. For many of us here in the United States, this week&#8217;s Thanksgiving holiday is a beloved annual occasion. It&#8217;s an opportunity to break bread with friends and family, reflect on the year together, and practice mindfulness and gratitude. You may also have heard that there&#8217;s food involvedâ€¦<img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-1376443\" src=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/thanksgiving_foods-665x444.jpg\" alt=\"A spread of Thanksgiving foods\" width=\"665\" height=\"444\" srcset=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/thanksgiving_foods-665x444.jpg 665w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/thanksgiving_foods-127x85.jpg 127w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/thanksgiving_foods-300x200.jpg 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/thanksgiving_foods-768x512.jpg 768w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/thanksgiving_foods-480x320.jpg 480w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/thanksgiving_foods-240x160.jpg 240w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/thanksgiving_foods-720x480.jpg 720w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/thanksgiving_foods.jpg 1024w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/thanksgiving_foods-430x287.jpg 430w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/thanksgiving_foods-645x430.jpg 645w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/thanksgiving_foods-460x307.jpg 460w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/thanksgiving_foods-600x400.jpg 600w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/thanksgiving_foods-500x333.jpg 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" />Food is essential in so many ways&#8211;it&#8217;s central to our cultural traditions, cherished in our childhood memories, and savored in our daily lives. Yet for many communities, it can be challenging to find local options for healthful, affordable family meals. For this Nonprofit Spotlight feature, we&#8217;ll be looking at one organization that&#8217;s hoping to change that. By championing food diversity and connecting families with resources for obtaining healthy, farm-fresh foods, they&#8217;re making a difference in the lives&#8211;and on the plates&#8211;of countless members of their community. Read on to learn more about this great nonprofit, and don&#8217;t forget to bring your appetite!</p>\n<hr />\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.citymarketbc.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">City Market</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.citymarketbc.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1376446\" src=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/logo-1-300x227.png\" alt=\"City Market logo\" width=\"300\" height=\"227\" srcset=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/logo-1-300x227.png 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/logo-1-300x227-112x85.png 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>The history of today&#8217;s City Market can be traced nearly as far back as 1837, with the official establishment of Bay City, Michigan on the borders of Lake Huron. Not long after, the original &#8220;City Market&#8221; began operations, serving townspeople and travelers alike with wares peddled from its open-air stalls.</p>\n<p>Today&#8217;s City Market is much changed from the humble beginnings of its namesake, entering the 21st century with a new nonprofit structure and an approach that seamlessly blends cuisine and community. A new indoor location in bustling downtown Bay City and over 40 local vendors means you&#8217;re sure to find whatever it is that you&#8217;re seeking. Sample handcrafted goods from artisan makers and explore delicious seasonal offerings in produce. And if your tummy&#8217;s rumbling after a bit of browsing, your next great meal can be had right at the market. Multiple quality restaurant options ensure that you&#8217;ll never have to leave hungry. Bon appetit!</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-1379570\" src=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/vegetables-2707860_1920-665x443.jpg\" alt=\"Produce at a farmers market\" width=\"665\" height=\"443\" srcset=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/vegetables-2707860_1920-665x443.jpg 665w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/vegetables-2707860_1920-128x85.jpg 128w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/vegetables-2707860_1920-300x200.jpg 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/vegetables-2707860_1920-768x512.jpg 768w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/vegetables-2707860_1920-480x320.jpg 480w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/vegetables-2707860_1920-240x160.jpg 240w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/vegetables-2707860_1920-720x480.jpg 720w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/vegetables-2707860_1920-1528x1016.jpg 1528w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/vegetables-2707860_1920-764x508.jpg 764w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/vegetables-2707860_1920-430x287.jpg 430w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/vegetables-2707860_1920-645x430.jpg 645w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/vegetables-2707860_1920-1068x712.jpg 1068w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/vegetables-2707860_1920-460x307.jpg 460w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/vegetables-2707860_1920-600x400.jpg 600w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/vegetables-2707860_1920-500x333.jpg 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></p>\n<p>There&#8217;s much more to today&#8217;s City Market than just a good day&#8217;s shopping, though. As part of its mission to make healthful eating more accessible for all, City Market is proud to welcome food assistance benefits and programs on behalf of its vendors. And once you&#8217;ve had your fill of culinary delights, you&#8217;ll find a host of events to enlighten and entertain, from cooking classes to educational seminars to seasonal spectacles for all ages. These events provide opportunities for small businesses and other nonprofits to promote their activities to the greater public, strengthening relationships within the community. And food-focused programming offers consumers the chance to expand their knowledge while benefitting from the tangible resources that City Market has to offer.</p>\n<p>Of course, connecting visitors with top-notch events is what we here at Modern Tribe do best, and we&#8217;re delighted to be City Market&#8217;s preferred choice for event management. In the Market Buzz section of City Market&#8217;s site, you&#8217;ll find a complete calendar of market events for your perusal. A clear visual hierarchy makes it easy to check event details at a glance, and our sleek, modern design means you won&#8217;t have to compromise aesthetics for functionality. Now that&#8217;s one sweet deal.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_1381700\" style=\"max-width: 640px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img class=\"wp-image-1381700 size-full\" src=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/city_market_calendar.png\" alt=\"Calendar display on City Market website\" width=\"630\" height=\"470\" srcset=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/city_market_calendar.png 630w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/city_market_calendar-114x85.png 114w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/city_market_calendar-300x224.png 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/city_market_calendar-260x195.png 260w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/city_market_calendar-430x321.png 430w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/city_market_calendar-460x343.png 460w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/city_market_calendar-600x448.png 600w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/11/city_market_calendar-500x373.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Source: City Market</p></div>\n<p>Hungry for more great content? There&#8217;s plenty more to enjoy over on City Market&#8217;s website, including vendor information, recipes for every season, and regular blog updates on a variety of topics. Head on over toÂ <a href=\"https://www.citymarketbc.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">citymarketbc.com</a> to check out the rest, and we&#8217;ll see you back here very soon!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/nonprofit-spotlight-city-market/\">Nonprofit Spotlight: City Market</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:52:\"Maintenance Release for the Week of 19 November 2017\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:83:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-for-the-week-of-19-november-2017/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 21 Nov 2017 21:55:46 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Products\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1388318\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:623:\"<p>Welcome to Maintenance Release number 23 of 2017! Here are some fixes and tweaks for you, to help your plugins run more smoothly. If this is your first time getting an update from us remember Maintenance Releases are smaller updates between major releases that are mostly comprised of bug Fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-for-the-week-of-19-november-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 19 November 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Neill\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5527:\"<p>Welcome to Maintenance Release number 23 of 2017! Here are some fixes and tweaks for you, to help your plugins run more smoothly. If this is your first time getting an update from us remember Maintenance Releases are smaller updates between major releases that are mostly comprised of bug Fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements. We always recommend using a staging site to test these changes before updating on a live site.</p>\n<p>To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#tec\">The Events Calendar 4.6.6</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ce\">Community Events 4.5.8</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ct\">Community Tickets 4.5.2</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#et\">Event Tickets 4.6.1</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#etp\">Event Tickets Plus 4.6.1</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"tec\">The Events Calendar 4.6.6</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Feature</strong> &#8211; Added Template class which adds a few layers of filtering to any template file included</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Add clear warnings and errors to prevent and limit the import of iCalendar sources missing required fields</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Included `tribe_callback_return` for static returns for Hooks</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Improve Aggregator notices including error data on the responses</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"ce\">Community Events 4.5.8</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Only display admin links in Community Tickets if user is able to access the admin</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"ct\">Community Tickets 4.5.2</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Fix New Ticket and New RSVP alignment </li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Only display admin links in Community Tickets if user is able to access the admin </li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Changed views: `community-tickets/modules/tickets`</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"et\">Event Tickets 4.6.1</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Prevents unnecessary AJAX requests when using tickets editor </li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Removes weird clearing of fields when canceling or saving Tickets </li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Allow saving of Ticket Editor contents when Updating the Event </li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Included more hooks via the new Template class for the Ticket Editor: `tribe_template_file`, `tribe_template_before_include`, `tribe_template_after_include` and `tribe_template_html` </li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Only display admin links in Community Tickets if user is able to access the admin </li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; spacing of message to logged in users to view attendees </li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; RSVP and Tickets migration from pre-4.6 updates capacity corretly for all cases now (props to Uwe Matern) </li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Attendees column for events display correctly the percentages now </li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Tickets Editor now has more support for Accessibility </li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added filters: `tribe_ticket_filter_attendee_report_link`, `tribe_tickets_attendees_show_title`</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Removed filters: `tribe_tickets_default_end_date`, `tribe_tickets_ajax_refresh_settings`, `tribe_tickets_can_update_ticket_price`, `tribe_tickets_disallow_update_ticket_price_message`, `tribe_events_tickets_metabox_edit_attendee`</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added actions: `tribe_tickets_save_post`</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Removed actions: `tribe_events_tickets_pre_ticket_list`, `tribe_events_tickets_post_ticket_list`</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Changed views: `tickets/email`, `tickets/orders-link`</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"etp\">Event Tickets Plus 4.6.1</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; EDD quantity styling to match WooCommerce and RSVP forms </li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Only display admin links in Community Tickets if user is able to access the admin </li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Add checkin status class to EDD to fix checkin button&#8217;s showing as disabled </li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Formats properly when displaying Unlimited capacity Tickets </li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Prevents deleted shared event capacity to still factor in when no tickets are sharing capacity </li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Updating capacity for the event all tickets gets Stock validation preventing Out of Stock message </li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added filters: `tribe_events_tickets_edd_display_ecommerce_links`, `tribe_filter_attendee_order_link`</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Removed filters: `tribe_events_tickets_woo_display_ecommerce_links`</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</h3>\n<p>The following plugins have not been updated this release and will remain at the version numbers specified here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Events Calendar PRO 4.4.19</li>\n<li>Filter Bar 4.5.1</li>\n<li>Image Widget 4.4.7</li>\n<li>Advanced Post Manager 4.4</li>\n<li>Eventbrite Tickets 4.4.8</li>\n<li>Image Widget Plus 1.0.2</li>\n<li>GigPress 2.3.19</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-for-the-week-of-19-november-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 19 November 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"Huge Savings â€“ Black Friday Sale\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/sale-black-friday-2017/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 21 Nov 2017 07:05:46 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Promotion\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1367453\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xm