b_iconbox icon=\"\" heading=\"HOME MADE, Truly, 100%\" animation=\"animation fade-in\" image=\"3141\"]One Day I\'ll be a grand\'ma and I will qualify for the memories of my kids\' children as \"my grand\'ma makes the best cakes\" [/thb_iconbox][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row column_padding=\"false\" row_padding=\"true\" thb_full_width=\"true\" type=\"full_width_content\" parallax_speed=\"1\" css=\".vc_custom_1466617452163{border-top-width: 1px !important;padding-top: 40px !important;border-top-color: #ececec !important;border-top-style: solid !important;}\" el_class=\"text-center\"][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\n[small_title title=\"WHO WE ARE\"]\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][thb_gap height=\"40\"][thb_slider navigation=\"true\" bullets=\"true\" images=\"3149,3150,3151,3152,3153,3154\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1411505599293{border-width: 0px 0px 1px !important;padding-top: 80px !important;padding-bottom: 80px !important;}\" type=\"in_container\" parallax_speed=\"1\"][vc_column][vc_column_text]<strong>Cook to Celebrate!</strong>\r\nCooking is the celebration of togetherness, sharing and creativity.\r\nDaria\'s vision is about sharing elegant and delicious creations with amateurs of intense, refined or delicate tastes, enthusiasts of wholesome ingredients and activists of slow food.\r\n\r\nGood food is made in small quantities, with all the passion and respect it deserves.\r\n\r\nGood food is meant to bring people together, stimulate memories of other great table moments and generate common memories for the future. Whenever someone will be heard quoting during a lunch, a diner or a tasting \"Oh, and do you remember this cake we had from Daria, how incredibly tasty and intense it was?!\" This is when the mission will be accomplished.\r\n\r\nEmotional memories stay with us for decades and Cook to Celebrate want to be part of them and, even better, to be a source of them!\r\n\r\nCook To Celebrate operates out of Daria\'s own kitchen in Den Haag. Her passion runs back to her childhood in Poland, enjoying the traditional cakes and cuisine of her mum and has been enriched with a good dose of French pastry making influence when she found out that the best cooking chocolate in the world, the one every three Michelin star chef mentions in their book, Valrhona, originates from a mere 20 km from her husband\'s native village. There couldn\'t have been better coincidence.\r\n\r\nOver the past few years, Daria has been on various pastry professional courses, with Lenotre in Paris and Versailles, with Valrhona in Tain l\'Hermitage and has been experimenting with recipes and ingredients at every opportunity, to the sheer enjoyment of her husband and children![/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1411505599293{border-width: 0px 0px 1px !important;padding-top: 80px !important;padding-bottom: 80px !important;}\" type=\"in_container\" parallax_speed=\"1\"][vc_column width=\"1/3\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h4>I don\'t like your floor, maty; it\'s too springy to my taste. I\'m used to ice-floors. I\'m sorry to throw cold water on the subject.</h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/3\"][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\nWith all his cruel ferocity and coldness there was an under of something in Tars Tarkas which he seemed ever battling to subdue. Could it be a vestige of some human instinct come back from an ancient forbear to haunt him with the horror of his people\'s ways!As I was approaching Dejah Thoris\' chariot I passed Sarkoja, and the black, venomous look she accorded me was the sweetest b alm I had felt for many hours. Lord, how she hated me! It bristled from her so palpably that one might almost have cut it with a sword. A few moments later I saw her deep in conversation with a warrior named Zad. Were you to give me your word that neither you nor Dejah Thoris would attempt to escape until after we have safely reached the court of Tal Hajus you might have the key and throw the chains into the river Iss. As I was approaching Dejah Thoris\' chariot I passed Sarkoja, and the black, venomous look she accorded me was the sweetest balm I had felt for many hours. Lord, how she hated me! It bristled from her so palpably that one might almost have cut it with a sword.\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/3\"][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\nWith all his cruel ferocity and coldness there was an under of something in Tars Tarkas which he seemed ever battling to subdue. Could it be a vestige of some human instinct come back from an ancient forbear to haunt him with the horror of his people\'s ways!As I was approaching Dejah Thoris\' chariot I passed Sarkoja, and the black, venomous look she accorded me was the sweetest b alm I had felt for many hours. Lord, how she hated me! It bristled from her so palpably that one might almost have cut it with a sword. A few moments later I saw her deep in conversation with a warrior named Zad. Were you to give me your word that neither you nor Dejah Thoris would attempt to escape until after we have safely reached the court of Tal Hajus you might have the key and throw the chains into the river Iss. As I was approaching Dejah Thoris\' chariot I passed Sarkoja, and the black, venomous look she accorded me was the sweetest balm I had felt for many hours. Lord, how she hated me! It bristled from her so palpably that one might almost have cut it with a sword.\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '156-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-20 16:21:24', '2017-09-20 16:21:24', '', 156, 'http://cloud1.gauravpanwar.com/156-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
